  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nThe lightchain integration test is not currently running in CI, so it breaks regularly, and for extended periods.\r\n\r\n(eg~ broken from #869 to #913)\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nInstructions for a manual local run are here: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/pull/913/files#diff-19d5ae6516fbe4a30f0bcc2f45e8dc00R36\r\n\r\nRun it locally first to be sure that tests pass on your master.\r\n\r\nOne time prep as described in the comment in the code linked above:\r\n- Set up geth with a >=11 blocks of `geth --testnet --syncmode full` (should happen essentially instantly after you find a peer). Try to run it as short as possible while still having the first 11 blocks\r\n- Note the `enode` in the geth logs\r\n- tar up the geth data dir (it should be very small with so few blocks)\r\n- add the geth data dir to a new file called `tests/p2p/integration/geth-data-ropsten.tar.gz`\r\n- move the lightchain integration test from `tests/p2p/test_lightchain_integration.py` to `tests/p2p/integration/test_lightchain.py`\r\n\r\nAdd a new circle job that runs just that integration test. In that job only:\r\n- untar the geth data dir\r\n- install geth, and cache it (see web3.py integration tests with geth for some examples)\r\n- run geth with discovery off: `geth --testnet --lightserv 90 --nodiscover`\r\n- run only this integration test `pytest --integration --capture=no --enode=\"enode://$ENODE_PUBKEY_FROM_EARLIER@127.0.0.1:30303\" tests/p2p/integration/test_lightchain.py`",
